verbose_text: The presence of the two alleles is the result of a G to T SNP (single nucleotide polymorphism) at the 5 ' splice site of the Wx intron 1, which causes an alternative splicing, thus reducing the production of functional enzymes in rice endosperm and determining the occurrence of low AAC amounts [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
